comments:
That part which until 1.4.1907 formed part of the parish of Northchurch. 
    See also Table 2, note (e).

Abolished 15.4.1898 to become the separate parishes of Great Berkhampstead 
    Urban and Great Berkhampstead Rural.

Created 1.4.1937 by renaming the parish of Great Berkhampstead 
    Urban. See also Table 2, note (l).

That part which until 1.4.1907 formed part of the parish of 
    Little Gaddesden. See also Table 2, note (h).

Created 15.4.1898 out of the rural part of the parish of Berkhampstead. 
    Abolished 1.4.1937 and divided between the parishes of Nettleden with Potten 
    End and Northchurch.

Created 15.4.1898 out of the part of the parish of Berkhampstead 
    in Great Berkhampstead Urban District. Renamed 1.4.1937 to become the parish 
    of Berkhamsted Urban.

Transferred from Buckinghamshire to Hertfordshire on 30.9.1895. 
    Abolished 1.4.1937 and added to the parish of Nettleden with Potten End. 
    See also Table 2, note (d).

Created 1.4.1937 out of the parishes of Nettleden, Great Berkhampstead 
    Rural and Northchurch. See also Table 2, note (l).

That part which until 1.4.1907 formed part of the parish of 
    Little Gaddesden. See also Table 2, note (h).

Abolished 1894 to become the separate parishes of Tring Urban 
    and Tring Rural. See also Table 2, note (a).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Tring. See also 
    Table 2, note (l).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Tring in Tring Urban 
    District. See also Table 2, note (l).
